03/08/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador-at-Large for War Crimes Issues Clint Williamson voiced Washington's full support for the work of the BiH Court and prosecutors, during a visit to the institutions' headquarters in Sarajevo on Wednesday (2 August). BiH Court President Meddzida Kreso says they discussed concrete assistance in resolving problems in the processing of war crimes cases. Williamson reiterated the importance of increased co-operation among courts in the region to close remaining war crimes cases. (Nezavisne novine - 03/08/06; RTRS, PBS BiH - 02/08/06)
